# Knowledge Graph

Created by [starter-brain](https://github.com/starter-brain/starter-brain) on ${date}.

## Format

Every entity is a markdown file in `entities/{type}/{slug}.md` with YAML frontmatter.

### Required frontmatter fields
- `type` — entity type (topic, insight, research, decision, pattern, person, project, hypothesis, or any string)
- `id` — unique identifier in `{type}/{slug}` format
- `name` — human-readable name
- `created` / `updated` — ISO dates
- `author` — who created it
- `status` — active, draft, validated, or archived

### Optional fields
- `confidence` — 0-100
- `importance` — 1-10 (default 5)
- `tags` — free-form list
- `relations` — typed links to other entities

### Relation types
REFERENCES, INFORMS, DERIVED_FROM, SUPERSEDED_BY, CONTRADICTS, DEPENDS_ON, PART_OF, USES_TOPIC, CREATED_BY (any string accepted)

### Episodes
Daily logs in `episodes/YYYY-MM-DD.md`. Format: `## author | HH:MM | type | importance:N`

Open this folder as an Obsidian vault to browse your knowledge graph visually.
